WEBVTT

00:01.022 --> 00:02.918
"The Block Party"

00:04.790 --> 00:08.150
<i>Here in the midwest,
fall is the best time of year.</i>

00:08.320 --> 00:11.860
<i>Corn mazes, football booster club,
and in our neighborhood,</i>

00:11.895 --> 00:13.808
<i>the Birchwood Avenue
Block Party.</i>

00:14.040 --> 00:17.111
<i>If you live between
321 and 452 Birchwood Avenue,</i>

00:17.146 --> 00:18.220
<i>you're more than welcome.</i>

00:18.410 --> 00:21.169
<i>But if you don't, well,
you're out of luck.</i>

00:22.890 --> 00:25.161
<i>But the most exciting thing
about the block party</i>

00:25.196 --> 00:27.029
<i>is the Birchwood 500--</i>

00:27.430 --> 00:30.465
<i>Three nail-biting laps around
the block on your riding mower.</i>

00:31.030 --> 00:32.674
<i>The whole neighborhood looks
forward to it,<i></i></i>

00:32.944 --> 00:34.039
<i>especially the kids.</i>

00:34.300 --> 00:35.866
Lawnmower races are lame.

00:36.290 --> 00:37.728
<i>Well, most of them,
anyway.</i>

00:38.130 --> 00:39.619
<i>Axl's in that phase
right now</i>

00:39.654 --> 00:41.564
<i>where everyone
and everything is lame.</i>

00:42.000 --> 00:43.274
Birthdays are lame.

00:44.490 --> 00:45.536
TV's lame.

00:46.250 --> 00:47.114
Food is lame.

00:48.220 --> 00:48.913
Hey.

00:49.043 --> 00:52.430
Last year, when Jack Meenahan won,
you said, "Don't worry, Dad.

00:52.465 --> 00:54.520
We'll get 'em next year."
<i>We.</i>

00:54.580 --> 00:55.860
And for that reason alone,

00:55.895 --> 00:57.145
I bet him
that the loser this year

00:57.180 --> 00:58.983
has to mow the other guy's
lawn for a year.

00:59.320 --> 01:00.617
Yeah, well,
that was lame.

01:01.570 --> 01:02.496
You know what's lame?

01:02.570 --> 01:04.250
Thinking
everything's lame is lame!

01:04.285 --> 01:06.537
- That's what's lame!
- Whatever!

01:07.580 --> 01:09.194
What I just yelled was lame,
wasn't it?

01:09.310 --> 01:11.825
Well, we're not allowed to yell
what we really want to.

01:18.280 --> 01:20.006
I'm supposed
to tell you something.

01:20.066 --> 01:21.358
It's important.

01:21.850 --> 01:23.230
<i>Important.</i>

01:24.160 --> 01:24.981
Well?

01:26.670 --> 01:29.640
They want to talk to you and Dad
about that test I had to take.

01:30.020 --> 01:32.541
- The Waterman-Ginsberg test?
- Yeah.

01:32.576 --> 01:34.644
Why'd I have
to take that test anyway?

01:34.896 --> 01:35.953
No reason.

01:36.160 --> 01:39.691
Then why'd they only give it to me
and the kid who sets things on fire?

01:40.440 --> 01:41.577
Mom, throw this.

01:43.400 --> 01:44.795
That was just
the day you took it.

01:44.865 --> 01:46.163
They give that test
to everyone.

01:46.520 --> 01:47.680
<i>They don't.</i>

01:48.260 --> 01:48.934
Throw it again.

01:50.220 --> 01:51.650
Wait.
Why am I doing this?

01:51.690 --> 01:53.947
Tryouts for tennis team
are next week. Yay!

01:54.550 --> 01:56.140
You're trying out
for tennis?

01:56.260 --> 01:58.188
No. Coach said
that's a long shot,

01:58.230 --> 02:00.359
but he did say there are
openings for ball girl.

02:00.509 --> 02:01.318
Yay!

02:07.030 --> 02:09.091
And I'm the one
who needs testing.

02:11.930 --> 02:13.893
<i>The reason Brick needed testing
was because...</i>

02:14.240 --> 02:17.405
<i>Well, the counselor explained it
so well, I'll let her tell it.</i>

02:17.680 --> 02:20.510
Brick's teachers referred him
for Waterman-Ginsberg testing

02:20.545 --> 02:23.301
because they observed that,
although very bright,

02:23.713 --> 02:25.308
your son struggles socially.

02:25.770 --> 02:29.684
In layman's terms, he has
a hard time making friends.

02:29.810 --> 02:31.930
We needed some $500 test
to tell us that?

02:31.965 --> 02:33.326
I could've told you that
for free.

02:33.426 --> 02:35.753
- Mike, let her finish.
- Thank you.

02:36.290 --> 02:38.992
The test revealed that
Brick is slightly challenged

02:39.027 --> 02:43.133
in his ability to establish
appropriate peer connections.

02:43.290 --> 02:44.460
I see.

02:45.260 --> 02:47.091
He has a hard time
making friends.

02:47.190 --> 02:48.183
Exactly.

02:49.200 --> 02:50.441
So there you have it.

02:52.860 --> 02:57.004
I-I think what my husband
and I are wondering is, why?

02:57.280 --> 02:59.550
Why does he have
a hard time making friends?

02:59.570 --> 03:02.571
Oh, who can say
why anyone does anything?

03:03.190 --> 03:05.332
You're supposed to,
for 500 bucks.

03:05.333 --> 03:07.120
Mike, let her finish.

03:07.681 --> 03:08.749
Oh, I'm done.

03:09.700 --> 03:10.856
Let me tell you something.

03:11.409 --> 03:13.638
Brick is
the happiest kid I know.

03:13.940 --> 03:15.624
Sure, he whispers
to himself.

03:15.710 --> 03:17.639
Sure,
he showers sitting down.

03:17.650 --> 03:20.521
Maybe he licked the car
once or twice.

03:21.190 --> 03:22.406
Hey, don't write
that down!

03:22.441 --> 03:24.083
I-I guess what
we were wondering is...

03:24.364 --> 03:26.422
Is there something
we should be doing?

03:27.420 --> 03:31.120
Well, what do you do now
to help him socialize?

03:34.100 --> 03:35.790
- I think--
- Shh!

03:38.290 --> 03:41.889
Oh, you know...
the usual.

03:42.380 --> 03:44.339
I'd do a little more
than that.

03:45.200 --> 03:47.622
So... should
we be concerned?

03:48.140 --> 03:50.650
I guess what I'd advise
is that you be concerned,

03:50.909 --> 03:52.568
but not overly concerned.

03:53.160 --> 03:56.092
Do what you can
and hope for the best.

03:56.500 --> 03:58.832
- That's it?
- That's it.

03:59.500 --> 04:00.683
Not so bad.

04:01.466 --> 04:03.820
Now doesn't it feel good
to have a plan?

04:06.610 --> 04:08.745
So how'd the kid
who lights things on fire do?

04:13.580 --> 04:16.704
<i>That stupid counselor meeting
left us more confused than ever.</i>

04:16.720 --> 04:18.471
<i>Why is everyone always
trying to convince you</i>

04:18.507 --> 04:19.890
<i>something's wrong
with your kids?</i>

04:19.899 --> 04:22.740
What is wrong with you?
That is for the block party.

04:22.780 --> 04:24.370
I can read.
I'm not stupid.

04:24.470 --> 04:26.298
We'll be the judge of
whether you're stupid or not.

04:26.333 --> 04:27.340
Now, I know
you own pants.

04:27.375 --> 04:28.723
I've seen them
draped over the TV.

04:28.966 --> 04:29.646
Go put 'em on.

04:32.840 --> 04:35.343
Oh, Mom, are you going
to the Booster Club thing

04:35.378 --> 04:36.471
at school on Friday?

04:37.810 --> 04:40.321
Well, I will
if you want me to.

04:40.720 --> 04:42.077
You sound like you do.

04:42.300 --> 04:44.642
You know,
that means so much to me.

04:44.677 --> 04:46.220
Oh, I miss you!

04:47.590 --> 04:48.957
Chill. Gross.

04:49.327 --> 04:50.958
Thought we talked
about this.

04:54.800 --> 04:56.177
What happened to him?

04:56.450 --> 04:58.400
I mean,
he used to be so sweet.

04:58.435 --> 04:59.495
Remember
when he was six

04:59.545 --> 05:01.392
and he made me
that clay giraffe?

05:02.490 --> 05:05.466
Thank you for being
the best mom ever.

05:07.170 --> 05:08.189
Should've kept that.

05:09.180 --> 05:10.417
So what are we gonna do?

05:10.470 --> 05:12.588
- About which one?
- The small one.

05:12.830 --> 05:13.342
I don't know.

05:13.392 --> 05:15.207
Maybe we didn't do
enough for Brick.

05:15.410 --> 05:16.223
He's a third kid.

05:16.410 --> 05:17.808
He's lucky
we remember to feed him.

05:21.680 --> 05:23.077
Looking good, Sue!

05:23.370 --> 05:24.894
She's trying out
for ball girl.

05:25.940 --> 05:28.365
Oh, I can't help thinking
it's my fault.

05:28.520 --> 05:29.846
She didn't make anything else.

05:30.160 --> 05:31.409
That's her fault--
not yours.

05:31.460 --> 05:32.663
No. We're on Brick now.

05:34.580 --> 05:35.715
Hard to keep track,
isn't it?

05:36.590 --> 05:38.384
I just feel like
I've slacked off.

05:38.430 --> 05:40.204
I used to try to set up
playdates for him,

05:40.255 --> 05:42.153
but I ran through every boy
in the neighborhood.

05:42.870 --> 05:43.693
I like juice.

05:45.510 --> 05:46.342
You do?

05:47.110 --> 05:49.361
Well, Brick likes juice, too,
don't you, Brick?

05:49.430 --> 05:51.841
Look at that!
Two juice-loving boys!

05:55.650 --> 05:56.398
Your move.

06:02.000 --> 06:05.050
Brick's catching up.
Going up the ladder...

06:05.085 --> 06:06.515
Good fun, huh, boys?

06:07.750 --> 06:09.104
I like juice, too.

06:11.780 --> 06:13.530
I hope you like
mint chocolate chip...

06:18.530 --> 06:20.429
Brick, what are you doing?

06:20.464 --> 06:21.849
You have a friend over.

06:21.960 --> 06:25.731
I just want a little privacy.
That kid is weird.

06:25.871 --> 06:26.869
<i>Weird.</i>

06:29.540 --> 06:32.269
Look, if you want, I can help
Brick make friends.

06:32.740 --> 06:33.900
But you know
what I'm gonna say.

06:33.935 --> 06:35.697
- Don't say it.
- Sports!

06:36.050 --> 06:37.456
There, I said it.

06:37.480 --> 06:38.541
Hey, Brick, get in here.

06:38.750 --> 06:39.778
This is Brick
we're talking about.

06:39.813 --> 06:40.540
He's gonna suck!

06:40.575 --> 06:41.406
Of course
he's gonna suck,

06:41.455 --> 06:43.404
but it's still the best way
for a boy to make friends.

06:44.320 --> 06:46.069
Hey, we're signing you
up for a team.

06:46.104 --> 06:46.952
What sport you like?

06:47.020 --> 06:48.070
I like basketball.

06:49.240 --> 06:51.425
See?
He likes basketball.

06:51.640 --> 06:52.879
That oughta be good
for some friends.

06:52.880 --> 06:54.185
Or get him beat up.

06:54.836 --> 06:55.669
By his friends.

06:57.730 --> 07:00.110
<i>Unfortunately, I couldn't make it
to Brick's first game</i>

07:00.145 --> 07:02.020
<i>because it was the same day
as Booster Club.</i>

07:02.180 --> 07:04.352
<i>I knew how important
it was to Axl</i>

07:04.387 --> 07:05.506
<i>for me to be there,</i>

07:05.560 --> 07:07.162
<i>and that made it
important to me.</i>

07:07.500 --> 07:09.393
<i>I had to suck up
every scrap of affection</i>

07:09.428 --> 07:10.597
<i>from him I could get.</i>

07:10.670 --> 07:12.560
Oh, yay, you're here!

07:12.870 --> 07:15.621
Barely. My boss thinks
I'm on a doughnut run.

07:15.622 --> 07:17.907
Remind me to steal some doughnuts
from the teachers' lounge.

07:18.110 --> 07:19.413
Oh, you can't, though.

07:19.448 --> 07:20.504
The boys
want to thank us

07:20.534 --> 07:22.320
for raising the money for
their new jerseys.

07:22.507 --> 07:23.572
It's a whole thing.

07:23.607 --> 07:24.560
It's a thing?

07:24.595 --> 07:26.796
Oh, that's why Axl
wanted me to come.

07:27.750 --> 07:32.048
- Um, isn't this Axl Heck's locker?
- That one.

